  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency health and nutrition assistance to IDPs and underserved population in Faryab province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the proposed project, Save the Children will implement integrated health and nutrition interventions in four hard to reach districts of Faryab province (Kohistan, Qaysar, Dawlat Abad and Shirin Tagab). Save the Children proposes to undertake the following key interventions: 

Health: Establish four emergency mobile health teams in Kohistan, Qaysar, Dawlat Abad and Shirin Tagab districts (one in each district) to provide primary and reproductive health, and psychosocial support services to IDPs, conflict-affected and underserved host communities with the particular focus on women and girls.  

Nutrition: Provide outpatient services for the management of severely and moderately acute malnourished (OPD-SAM and OPD-MAM) boys and girls (six to 59 months),  management of acutely malnourished pregnant and lactating women (PLW), and provision of  infant and young child feeding in emergency (IYCF-E) services through four integrated emergency mobile teams (same teams with health) in Kohistan, Qaysar, Dawlat Abad and Shirin Tagab districts. To build resilience of vulnerable groups at  borderline of acute malnutrition, children at risk of malnutrition with MUAC gt12.5 - lt13.5 will be targeted for integrated IYCF-E response. 
The proposed four districts are amongst the hard to reach districts identified by the Humanitarian Access Group (HAG). This project is designed in line with the health and nutrition clusters strategic priorities, and is based on a rapid needs assessment conducted by Save the Children. The project will focus on addressing the acute humanitarian needs in these four hard to reach districts. 
The proposed action will target 36,000 direct beneficiaries including 18,016 women and girls. The timeline for the action is from 1 May 2020 until 30 April 2021. Save the Children will implement this project in coordination with all relevant actors at the national, provincial and community levels to ensure effective and timely management of the proposed interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
